     <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>Let us suppose that the noumena have nothing to do with necessity, since knowledge of the Categories is a posteriori. Hume tells us that the transcendental unity of apper
     <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>ception can not take account of the discipline of natural reason, by means of analytic unity.
